{"word":"Σιών","slug":"Σιών","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>Σιών, ἡ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Heb.\">Heb.</a>] <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ indecl.\">indecl.</a> <b>Sion<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> of <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Mt.\">Mt.</a> Sion in Jerusalem <b><a href='B:730 14:1'>Rv 14:1</a>;</b> in imagery <b><a href='B:650 12:22'>Hb 12:22</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> in <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ transf.\">transf.</a> sense of a: Jerusalem and its inhabitants <b><a href='B:470 21:5'>Mt 21:5</a>; <a href='B:500 12:15'>J 12:15</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>c.</pp></b> in extended sense of b: the people of God or Israel <b><a href='B:520 9:33'>Ro 9:33</a>; <a href='B:520 11:26'>11:26</a>;</b> constituted as the new messianic Jerusalem <b><a href='B:670 2:6'>1 Pt 2:6</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:Σιχάρ\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:σιωπάω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}